Author: OodietcokeheadoO
Text: They need to stop talking about the Ed health side effects! It makes us all feel worse about ourselves than magazines and media I swear! No body says "oh it's not psychotic depression so it must not be very severe." "Oh it's a manic episode but he doesn't hallucinate and is only a little grandiose so whatever" but with eds it doesn't feel valid until we're dying.

Author: ifuckpineapples
Text: yuuup, in all the years ive been restricting the only nonnormal result ive had on a bloodtest was high bilirubin, which they said was nothing to worry about and probably from my bc pills. i think once a few years ago my blood pressure was a bit low but fine? medically speaking apparently im fine, even when i feel like death. great.
